-- Spain’s FADE Said to Plan Sale of Four-Year Bonds in Euros
-- B y   H a n n a h   B e n j a m i n
-- 2012-01-23T09:51:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-23/spain-s-fade-said-to-plan-sale-of-four-year-bonds-in-euros.html
FADE,  Spain ’s Electricity Deficit
Amortization Fund, plans to sell four-year bonds in euros,
according to a banker involved in the transaction.  The bonds may be priced to yield about 70 basis points more
than Spanish government debt, the banker said. Citigroup Inc.,
Credit Agricole CIB, Credit Suisse Group AG, Deutsche Bank AG,
HSBC Holdings Plc and  Banco Santander SA (SAN)  are managing the deal.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Hannah Benjamin in London at 
